  "original_title": "\u0b8e\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf \u0b89\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbf \u0b87\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The officer who kicked the eddy pauses",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lankan Army announced today (05) that the military officer who kicked a civilian at a fuel station in Yakkapitiya, Kurunegala has been suspended from all duties.",
        "A statement issued by the Army stated that the lieutenant colonel has been suspended from all duties pending the completion of investigations into the incident.",
        "This decision has been taken on the recommendation of Army Commander Lt. Gen. Vikum Lianake.",
        "The accused military officer has been immediately suspended from all duties pending the recommendations of the 5-member court of inquiry.",
        "Investigations were initiated after a video of an army officer kicking a commoner went viral on social media.",
        "According to the owner and officials of the filling station, it was revealed that a group present at the filling station had disrupted the operations of the station.",
        "It is reported that he interfered with the duties of the army and police on duty and abused them with inappropriate words.",
        "It is noteworthy that the spokesperson said that the authorities suspect that this group may have deliberately created unrest at the fuel station and called for a clash and two people have been arrested in connection with the incident."
      ],
